Defendant Justin C. Chmiel in court with Attorney Jonathan A. Lavoy.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Becky Van Dam appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant entered a  guilty plea to Count #3.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #3.  Counts #1 & 2 are dismissed and read-in.  Victim makes statements. State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Lavoy makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #3: WITHHELD SENTENCE:   

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR       *CONCURRENT*

CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs 
____No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
____Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are 
prescribed/sign releases
____Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____No violent or abusive contact with: victim
____Domestic Violence Counseling through a State Certified Batterers Intervention Program such as Alliance Counseling or Family Services of Waukesha;


COSTS:  $343.00  (to be paid out of cash bail posted and remainder to be returned to poster) - Court waives the DNA Surcharge 


CONDITION TIME:  60 Days - STAYED - to be used at agent's discretion
